  "page": "A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 39",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;background-color:rgb(230, 230, 230)\">Jon VIII</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i> chapter</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/A_dance_with_dragons\" title=\"A dance with dragons\"><img alt=\"ADanceWithDragons.jpg\" src=\"/images/7/79/ADanceWithDragons.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"337\" class=\"thumbborder\" /></a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">POV</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon Snow</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Place</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Castle_Black\" title=\"Castle Black\">Castle Black</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Page</th><td>\n514 <small>UK HC</small> <small>(<a href=\"/index.php/Chapters_Table_of_contents\" title=\"Chapters Table of contents\">Other versions</a>)</small></td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;background-color:rgb(230, 230, 230)\">Chapter chronology <small>(<a href=\"/index.php/Chapters\" title=\"Chapters\">All</a>)</small></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_35\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 35\">Jon VII</a><br />↑</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<table style=\"width:100%;\"><tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"width:33%; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;\"><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_38\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 38\">The Watcher</a></td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:middle;\">&#160;←</td>\n<td style=\"width:33%; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; padding-right:0.1em; padding-left:0.1em;\">Jon VIII</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:middle;\">→&#160;</td>\n<td style=\"width:33%; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;\"><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_40\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 40\">Tyrion IX</a></td>\n</tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n↓<br /><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_44\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 44\">Jon IX</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon Snow</a> sends <a href=\"/index.php/Val\" title=\"Val\">Val</a> to find <a href=\"/index.php/Tormund_Giantsbane\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Tormund Giantsbane\">Tormund Giantsbane</a> and offer him and his followers shelter south of the <a href=\"/index.php/Wall\" title=\"Wall\">Wall</a>. Jon then meets with officers of the <a href=\"/index.php/Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Night&#39;s Watch\">Night's Watch</a> who disagree with his decisions.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Synopsis\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Synopsis</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Character_list\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Character list</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Mentions\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Mentions</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Notes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Notes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Synopsis\">Synopsis</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_39&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Synopsis\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tleft\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:252px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Denkata5698_Val.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/e/eb/Denkata5698_Val.jpg/250px-Denkata5698_Val.jpg\" width=\"250\" height=\"393\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/e/eb/Denkata5698_Val.jpg 1.5x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Denkata5698_Val.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Val\" title=\"Val\">Val</a> by Denkata5698 ©</div></div></div>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon</a> sends <a href=\"/index.php/Val\" title=\"Val\">Val</a> north into the <a href=\"/index.php/Haunted_forest\" title=\"Haunted forest\">haunted forest</a> to find <a href=\"/index.php/Tormund_Giantsbane\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Tormund Giantsbane\">Tormund Giantsbane</a> and offer him and his followers shelter south of the <a href=\"/index.php/Wall\" title=\"Wall\">Wall</a>. Jon explains that Val's lover <a href=\"/index.php/Jarl\" title=\"Jarl\">Jarl</a> had been killed by the Wall, not by him. Val reveals that she has given the milk name <a href=\"/index.php/Monster\" title=\"Monster\">Monster</a> to the son of <a href=\"/index.php/Gilly\" title=\"Gilly\">Gilly</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Craster\" title=\"Craster\">Craster</a>, and she advises Jon to keep the child away from <a href=\"/index.php/Melisandre\" title=\"Melisandre\">Melisandre</a>. Val says she will return the first night of the full <a href=\"/index.php/Moon\" title=\"Moon\">moon</a>.\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Dolorous_Edd\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Dolorous Edd\">Dolorous Edd</a> brings Jon his dinner in the new <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Commander_of_the_Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Lord Commander of the Night&#39;s Watch\">Lord Commander's</a> chambers behind the armory of <a href=\"/index.php/Castle_Black\" title=\"Castle Black\">Castle Black</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/Bowen_Marsh\" title=\"Bowen Marsh\">Bowen Marsh</a>, Septon <a href=\"/index.php/Cellador\" title=\"Cellador\">Cellador</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Othell_Yarwyck\" title=\"Othell Yarwyck\">Othell Yarwyck</a> talk to Jon with various complaints; they disapprove of <a href=\"/index.php/Leathers\" title=\"Leathers\">Leathers</a> as Castle Black's <a href=\"/index.php/Master-at-arms\" title=\"Master-at-arms\">master-at-arms</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Satin\" title=\"Satin\">Satin</a> as Jon's steward, and Jon's decision to negotiate with Tormund and allow him and his men through the Wall. They are also nervous about the fact Jon is keeping two corpses in the <a href=\"/index.php/Ice_cell\" title=\"Ice cell\">ice cells</a>, and react with outrage and horror when Jon reveals he is waiting for them to rise, ignoring Jon's argument that the Watch knows next to nothing about the <a href=\"/index.php/Wights\" title=\"Wights\">wights</a> or their masters, and need to learn more if they are to defeat them.\n</p><p>Overlooking the officers' protests, Jon tells them of a large group of <a href=\"/index.php/Wildlings\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Wildlings\">wildlings</a> making for <a href=\"/index.php/Hardhome\" title=\"Hardhome\">Hardhome</a> on the eastern coast of the lands <a href=\"/index.php/Beyond_the_Wall\" title=\"Beyond the Wall\">beyond the Wall</a>, following the <a href=\"/index.php/Woods_witch\" title=\"Woods witch\">woods witch</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Mother_Mole\" title=\"Mother Mole\">Mother Mole</a> who claims they will find ships there to bring them across the <a href=\"/index.php/Narrow_sea\" title=\"Narrow sea\">narrow sea</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;N 1&#93;</a></sup> Jon fears they will die there, but when he gets only indifference from the others at the prospect of thousands of dead wildlings, Jon finally loses patience. Angrily asking if they do not realize the truth or are just ignoring it, Jon points out that if they do nothing, the wildlings at Hardhome will die in their thousands, and when they are dead, in time they will rise up again with blue eyes and cold hands, and the <a href=\"/index.php/Others\" title=\"Others\">Others</a> will have thousands more wights under their control to send at the Wall.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Character_list\">Character list</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_39&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Character list\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<table class=\"wikitable\" width=\"100%\">\n\n<tbody><tr valign=\"top\">\n<td style=\"width:50;\">\n<p><b>Appearing:</b>\n</p>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Cellador\" title=\"Cellador\">Cellador</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Half-blind_garron\" title=\"Half-blind garron\">Half-blind garron</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Bowen_Marsh\" title=\"Bowen Marsh\">Bowen Marsh</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Mormont%27s_raven\" title=\"Mormont&#39;s raven\">Mormont's raven</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Mully\" title=\"Mully\">Mully</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon Snow</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Eddison_Tollett\" title=\"Eddison Tollett\">Eddison Tollett</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Val\" title=\"Val\">Val</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Othell_Yarwyck\" title=\"Othell Yarwyck\">Othell Yarwyck</a></li></ul>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width:50;\">\n<p><b>Mentioned:</b>\n</p>\n<div style=\"column-count:2; column-widt